  "text": "The sensitivity of DH c and DH d to the model parameters is shown in Fig. 6 . In this Figure, we used the term DH crit as a term relevant to both DH c and DH d . All parameter variations were carried out by varying a base case shown in all plots of Fig. 6 . The base case corresponds to the system shown in Fig. 5c and d. Both DH c and DH d appear approximately proportional to the hydraulic conductivity of the clogging layer, K c , and also to the depth of ponding, d. Inverse relationships between DH c and DH d , and K a and h c are also apparent. These relationships are independent of the location of the observation point. Similar sensitivities were obtained for a river system by [CITATION_1] ",
